  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Subjects in the Intensive Care Unit
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        20 subjects, minimum age 18 years, who are anticipated to be on an insulin infusion for 3-7
        consecutive days. 10 of these subjects will be on vasopressors who will be receiving large
        volume fluid resuscitation. It is possible that these subjects will have either altered
        microcirculation (vasopressors) or interstitial fluid dynamics (fluid resuscitation) that
        would affect the accuracy of the measurement. If it is shown to be accurate in all of these
        subjects, we will conclude that is will be accurate in all ICU subjects.

        -

        Exclusion Criteria:

        subjects not on insulin infusion and/or younger than 18 years

        -
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
